                    <span>If a man or a woman reads the first chapter, and fear or deep sadness come up, this intensive workbook may be a path to deep healing. Gurian displays an enlightened understanding of the mother/son relationship in the theory portion of the book. Following a mythopoetic metaphor, the second half workbook will put a dedicated man well on the way to reclaiming his masculinity from his shadow. Men and women will gain more compassion and understanding of the opposite sex. An excellent book when coupled with a willingess on the reader's part to not get immersed in the study of wounds, and to move on in life through action.</span>
                  
              
